The paper discusses the need for automated management and analysis of heterogeneous data within the complete cannabinoids domain, which involves experts from various fields such as biochemistry, chemistry, psychology, and social sciences. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of cs.DB (database), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), cs.LG (machine learning), cs.IR (information retrieval), and cs.CY (cybersecurity), as these sub-categories are relevant to data management, analysis, and integration across diverse sources.
